10:09.516 --> 10:10.850
so I'll coordinate with you
the details, okay, John?

10:10.943 --> 10:12.518
That sounds excellent.

10:12.603 --> 10:13.695
John, thanks for sharing
all of that with us.

10:13.854 --> 10:15.104
- Much appreciated.
- Yeah.

10:15.189 --> 10:16.948
- MATTY: Thanks John.
- GARY: Thank you, John.

10:17.107 --> 10:18.241
JOHN B.:
All right, guys, take care.

10:23.205 --> 10:24.697
NARRATOR: Three days
after his meeting

10:24.782 --> 10:27.200
with the Laginas and
Gary Drayton on Oak Island,

10:27.293 --> 10:30.378
Matty Blake has traveled
to Sebastian, Florida

10:30.537 --> 10:34.374
some 90 miles
southeast of Orlando.

10:34.458 --> 10:36.384
John, good to see you again.

10:36.469 --> 10:37.710
It's good to be back
on the Treasure Coast.

10:37.795 --> 10:39.304
- Welcome aboard.
- NARRATOR: At the headquarters

10:39.463 --> 10:43.549
of the 1715 Fleet-Queens Jewels,
LLC,

10:43.643 --> 10:46.978
Matty is meeting with
operations manager John Brandon

10:47.137 --> 10:50.723
in preparation to join a search
for some $1 billion

10:50.808 --> 10:52.567
in sunken Spanish treasure.

10:52.726 --> 10:54.319
This is our lab here

10:54.403 --> 10:56.229
where we, uh,
bring the artifacts

10:56.322 --> 10:57.822
and the things that are found
out there in the ocean,

10:57.907 --> 10:59.482
for conservation purposes.

10:59.575 --> 11:01.159
Hopefully,
over the next couple of days

11:01.318 --> 11:03.820
when we are out with Greg,
he'll make some finds,

11:03.904 --> 11:05.571
and we'll be bringing them
back here to, uh,

11:05.656 --> 11:07.156
to do the conservation work.

