21:23.023 --> 21:25.024
A couple of them,
the shell's so hard, you know.

21:25.117 --> 21:27.118
You can't even get your fingers
into it to dig around it,

21:27.277 --> 21:29.361
so I needed the knife
just to poke holes.

21:29.454 --> 21:32.197
They look like ship material,
ship pins and things,

21:32.282 --> 21:34.208
-so it's, uh, it's a good sign. Yeah.
-GREG: It looks good.

21:34.293 --> 21:36.869
JOHN B.: When you do an
excavation and find something,

21:36.962 --> 21:39.288
even if it's only
a single iron ship's spike,

21:39.372 --> 21:41.123
but it's something that
you're fairly certain is

21:41.207 --> 21:42.624
from the wreck,

21:42.718 --> 21:44.376
then that level of excitement
goes up,

21:44.461 --> 21:45.803
because you know you're close.

21:45.962 --> 21:47.463
You know you're in
the debris field.

21:47.556 --> 21:49.381
So it's very, very exciting.

21:49.466 --> 21:51.142
And that'll lead you
to the major finds.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.230
Wind's picking up a little bit.
It's starting to get choppy,

21:56.315 --> 21:59.725
so this might be our last dive.
So, uh, give it hell.

21:59.809 --> 22:01.068
MATTY:
Go get 'em.

22:08.735 --> 22:09.827
Copy that.

22:20.922 --> 22:23.174
That's not what we wanted
to hear, fellas.

22:23.258 --> 22:26.585
NARRATOR: Although the team
has made great progress so far,

22:26.678 --> 22:28.253
continued diving

22:28.338 --> 22:31.015
in the deteriorating
visibility conditions

22:31.174 --> 22:34.518
could lead to danger
rather than good fortune.

22:34.677 --> 22:36.595
With the weather picking up
a little bit,

22:36.679 --> 22:38.773
it's about to come off shore.

22:38.932 --> 22:40.858
It's probably better if we, uh,
play it safe and head in.

22:40.942 --> 22:45.029
NARRATOR: Weather permitting, the
search will have to continue tomorrow.

22:45.188 --> 22:46.188
So, we got to call
this one short,

22:46.281 --> 22:48.357
but I am really encouraged

22:48.450 --> 22:50.117
by the finds that they made.

22:50.276 --> 22:52.611
Uh, the fact that we pulled up
anything out of the water,

22:52.695 --> 22:54.196
never mind things
that look like they're

22:54.289 --> 22:55.456
part of the Treasure Fleet.

22:55.540 --> 22:57.449
I'm really ready to go tomorrow.

22:57.534 --> 22:58.959
- Great job.
- Tomorrow's the day.

22:59.044 --> 22:59.877
All right, tomorrow's the day.

